r"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Short-term+follow-up+results+in+795+nonpalpable+probably+benign+lesions+detected+at+screening+mammography&amp;author=I+Vizca%C3%ADno&amp;author=L+Gadea&amp;author=L+Andreo&amp;publication_year=2001&amp;journal=Radiology&amp;pages=475-483&amp;doi=10.1148%2Fradiology.219.2.r01ma11475&amp;pmid=11323475">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">6.</div><div id="r6" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Varas X, Leborgne F, Leborgne JH. Nonpalpable, probably benign lesions: role of follow-up mammography. <em>Radiology</em> 1992;184(2):409–414.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/radiology.184.2.1620838">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/1620838/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Nonpalpable%2C+probably+benign+lesions%3A+role+of+follow-up+mammography&amp;author=X+Varas&amp;author=F+Leborgne&amp;author=JH+Leborgne&amp;publication_year=1992&amp;journal=Radiology&amp;pages=409-414&amp;doi=10.1148%2Fradiology.184.2.1620838&amp;pmid=1620838">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">7.</div><div id="r7" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Lehman CD, Rutter CM, Eby PR, White E, Buist DS, Taplin SH. Lesion and patient characteristics associated with malignancy after a probably benign finding on community practice mammography. <em>AJR Am J Roentgenol</em> 2008;190(2):511–515.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.2214/AJR.07.2153">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18212240/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Lesion+and+patient+characteristics+associated+with+malignancy+after+a+probably+benign+finding+on+community+practice+mammography&amp;author=CD+Lehman&amp;author=CM+Rutter&amp;author=PR+Eby&amp;author=E+White&amp;author=DS+Buist&amp;author=SH+Taplin&amp;publication_year=2008&amp;journal=AJR+Am+J+Roentgenol&amp;pages=511-515&amp;doi=10.2214%2FAJR.07.2153&amp;pmid=18212240">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">8.</div><div id="r8" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Chung CS, Giess CS, Gombos EC, et al. Patient compliance and diagnostic yield of 18-month unilateral follow-up in surveillance of probably benign mammographic lesions. <em>AJR Am J Roentgenol</em> 2014;202(4):922–927.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.2214/AJR.13.11137">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24660725/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Patient+compliance+and+diagnostic+yield+of+18-month+unilateral+follow-up+in+surveillance+of+probably+benign+mammographic+lesions&amp;author=CS+Chung&amp;author=CS+Giess&amp;author=EC+Gombos&amp;publication_year=2014&amp;journal=AJR+Am+J+Roentgenol&amp;pages=922-927&amp;doi=10.2214%2FAJR.13.11137&amp;pmid=24660725">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">9.</div><div id="r9" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Taboada JL, Stephens TW, Krishnamurthy S, Brandt KR, Whitman GJ. The many faces of fat necrosis in the breast. <em>AJR Am J Roentgenol</em> 2009;192(3):815–825.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.2214/AJR.08.1250">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pu